`crates/` currently holds a single member, `steno/` — the theory-compiler library, its four consuming binaries, and its test suite. There is no workspace-level intent.md, so this directory's contract is whatever `steno/` exposes: source `.steno` files in, Plover dictionaries / LSP snippets / `@literal` keystroke sequences out, via the pipeline re-exported from `steno`'s `lib.rs`.

With only one crate present, there is no cross-crate coupling, shared build config, or workspace-wide invariant to document here — everything an editor needs (the parse/expand/editor pipeline contract, the `dict.steno` corpus dependency shared between the library and its tests, the terminal/non-terminal stroke classification duplicated between `render`/`snippet` and their test guards) is already stated in `steno/rollup.ctx`. A typical change starts inside `steno/src/`, not at this level.